parameters: H-H-Hikaru! Please don't leave me behind!

In the dark cave, only the sound of droplets falling can
be heard.

I'm not sure if it's because the battery is running low or
if the output is weak to begin with, but the light from
the flashlight was too dim to dispel the darkness.

If I had a Chimchar, I could have at least used flash but
the guy behind me is just a regular monkey that doesn't
serve any purpose.

Due to the cool air inside the cave, or perhaps because
there really is something in here, my spine shivers.
Why am I doing this courage test with Saruyama right now?

Isn't the courage test supposed to be the main event
of the training camp?
A droplet fell on my neck.
Don't scream over something like that!
You're making me freak out too!
B-Because it's scary, Hikaru should go first.
B-Because it's scary, Hikaru should go first.
I can hear a dripping sound...

This cave surprisingly spacious. There's even a small
stream in here.

I know it's a bit late to think about it, but honestly,
wouldn't it be dangerous if we got trapped here?
Shouldn't we turn around and leave right now...?
Oh, Hikaru, there's something over there!

It may be a late thought, but honestly, isn't it
dangerous to be trapped like this?
Shouldn't we turn around and leave right now...?
Oh, Hikaru, there's something over there!

There was a sign placed where Saruyama pointed, just before
it broke.

This place above is the secret base of the Earth Defense
Force! Ordinary people must absolutely not enter! Showa
63, Earth Defense Force Red, Sakamoto Justice.
No, more importantly, the name is really weird.
Without a doubt, there's treasure buried in this cave!
No, isn't that just stealing if you think about it?

If I attend school with Saruyama, my brain might turn
into a 'tsukkomi' brain.
The fear of having a 'tsukkomi' brain...! (laughs)
All I can ever hear is 'tsukkomi' now!

Thanks to Saruyama making a fuss about treasure,
it feels like the gloomy interior of the cave has
become a little brighter.
There must be a secret passage somewhere...!

A secret passage... There's no way something like that
exists...
Step on this and jump up like a hero!

If you want to go to the secret base of the Earth Defense
Force, you have to put in some effort!
We need to do something quickly...
Oh, ho! Treasure, wait for me!

And then, Saruyama climbed up like a monkey on a tree,
making strange cheers as he went up.
Huh? There's a path here too.

I mentally question why the ladder is above instead of
below.
The name 'Secret' Base is too faithful...

I can't believe the fact that no matter how much I think
about it, this person has the same intelligence level
as me.
And then Saruyama carefully opened the old box.

However, when the box opened with a squeaky sound, all that
could be glimpsed inside was darkness.
In other words, the box was empty.

Treasure chests in secret bases are usually like
that, but disappointing nonetheless.
Well, I thought it would turn out like this.
Treasure... Hikaru, aren't you an idiot?
Ah, w-wait!? What are you doing all of a sudden!

I hit Saruyama, who made me go through all this trouble,
with all my might.

As I watched Saruyama, who was avoiding me and trying to
escape, engage in a messy struggle, I tilted my head,
feeling somewhat bothered. And in that moment, I saw
something sparkling in the box.

I crouched down and picked up the ring, wiping it with
my hem.

This copper ring, without any big scratches or rust, must
be old.
There must be somewhere to use it.

I silently expressed my gratitude to the last Earth
Defense Force member of the Showa era and took the ring
with me.
